ing: 1 fresh poblano chile pepper, seeded and chopped
1 (15 ounce) can black beans, rinsed and drained
des: "A light lunch, or serve with cheese and tortillas. Also good as a side dish with your favorite Mexican food."
ins: Heat olive oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat. Add onion and garlic, and cook, stirring until translucent. Add zucchini and poblano pepper, and saute until soft. Stir in corn and beans, and heat through. Season with salt to taste.
